[h1]Associative Arrays[/h1]

[b]Associative [/b]arrays are arrays that use named keys that you assign to them.
There are two ways to create an associative array: [code format="php"]$people = array("David"=>"27", "Amy"=>"21", "John"=>"42");
// or
$people['David'] = "27";
$people['Amy'] = "21";
$people['John'] = "42";[/code]
[note]In the first example, note the use of the  [b]=>[/b] signs in assigning values to the named keys.[/note]

quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to output the age from the array.
[!raw!]
<?php
$man = array("name"=>"John", "age"=>"25");
echo $man['{0}'];
?>

